{% if python != 'none' %}
- `python.yml` — Python conventions, applied to `{% if python == 'root' %}src/**/*.py{% else %}backend/src/**/*.py{% endif %}`
{% endif %}

## Ephemeral artifacts

`.ai/` is gitignored. Use it freely for scratch notes, plans, and intermediate research. Never reference `.ai/` paths in committed files.

## Secrets and environment variables

{% if secrets == 'sops' %}
Secrets are managed with [SOPS](https://getsops.io/). Encrypted secret files are committed to the repo. You need the appropriate age or GPG key configured locally to decrypt them.

**Never write plaintext secrets to any file.** Use `sops <file>` to edit encrypted files in place. See [docs/operations.md](docs/operations.md) for key setup instructions.
{% elif secrets == 'env-only' %}
Secrets are passed via environment variables. Copy `.env.example` to `.env` (which is gitignored) and fill in real values.

**Never commit `.env`.**
{% else %}
No secrets management is configured. Credentials are injected by the deployment environment (CI secrets, Kubernetes secrets, etc.). Do not hardcode credentials anywhere in the repository.
{% endif %}

